.TH "NAVIGATIONDESTINATION.SAMEDOCUMENT" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationDestination.sameDocument \- NavigationDestination:
sameDocument property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]sameDocument\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigationDestination\f[R] interface returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if
the navigation is to the same \f[CR]document\f[R] as the current
\f[CR]Document\f[R] value, or \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
.PP
This is useful for checking whether the navigation will be
same\-document or cross\-document.
.SH VALUE
A boolean.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(event.destination.sameDocument);
});
.EE
